title: President Tebboune receives Malian counterpart, Bah N'Daw
text: President of the Republic, Mr Abdelmadjid Tebboune, received Sunday in Algiers Head of State of Mali, Mr Bah N'Daw who is on a working visit to Algeria.

The meeting took place at the headquarters of the Presidency of the Republic, in the presence of Private Principal Secretary at the Presidency of the Republic Mr Noureddine Bardad-Daidj, Foreign Minister Mr Sabri Boukadoum, Minister of Interior, Local Authorities and National Planning, Mr Kamel Beldjoud, as well as Lieutenant General Mr Sa√Ød Chanegriha, Chief of Staff of the National People's Army.

The Malian Head of State arrived Saturday in Algiers for a two-day working visit during which he will discuss with President Tebboune bilateral relations between Algeria and Mali, as well as ways and means to develop them in the best interests of both countries.
